# DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW — CVE-2026-0284
#
# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the
# CVE/advisory description only.
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline —
# this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# SEVERITY DISCREPANCY NOTICE:
#   [1] NVD scores this CVSS 9.9 (CRITICAL).
#   [3] CVE.org (CNA-published, CVSS v4.0) scores this 4.7 (MEDIUM).
#   Analysts MUST review both scores before acting on priority tier.
#   The CNA (Palo Alto Networks) advisory [2] independently rates
#   severity as MEDIUM. The NVD 9.9 CRITICAL score may reflect a
#   broader worst-case interpretation. Do not rely solely on the
#   NVD score for triage decisions.
#
# Detection rationale:
#   CVE-2026-0284 is an XML injection in the PAN-OS Large Scale VPN
#   (LSVPN) component, reachable by unauthenticated network attackers
#   with no user interaction required [1][2]. LSVPN satellite/portal
#   communication typically occurs over HTTPS to PAN-OS management or
#   data-plane endpoints. XML injection payloads commonly introduce
#   crafted XML metacharacters or entity references (e.g., <, >, &,
#   XML entity declarations, or CDATA blocks) within HTTP request
#   bodies targeting LSVPN-related URI paths. No LSVPN-specific URI
#   paths or packet structure were published in the advisory [2] at
#   time of rule authorship; the content matches below are therefore
#   heuristic and require analyst tuning against the target environment.
#   PAN-OS LSVPN portal/satellite endpoints commonly appear under
#   /ssl-vpn/ or /global-protect/ URI namespaces; adjust $HTTP_PORTS
#   and URI content to match your deployment.
#
# Limitations:
#   - No PoC or PCAP available; match logic is advisory-derived only.
#   - Traffic is expected to be TLS-encrypted in production; this rule
#     will only fire on plaintext or decrypted (SSL-inspected) sessions.
#   - High false-positive potential: XML metacharacters appear in
#     legitimate traffic. Tune pcre and content to narrow scope.
#   - is_kev is set to false; CVE-2026-0284 is not listed in the CISA
#     KEV catalog at time of authorship. Update if status changes.
#
alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET $HTTP_PORTS (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-0284 PAN-OS LSVPN XML injection attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.method; content:"POST";
  http.uri; content:"/ssl-vpn/"; nocase;
  http.request_body;
  pcre:"/(?:<!ENTITY\s|<!DOCTYPE\s[^>]*\[|<!\[CDATA\[|[\x00-\x08\x0b\x0c\x0e-\x1f]|(?:%3C|<)[^>]*(?:ENTITY|DOCTYPE|CDATA)[^>]*(?:%3E|>))/i";
  reference:cve,2026-0284;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:web-application-attack; sid:9000004; rev:1; )

